The paper deals with computer vision tasks, specifically large-scale image retrieval, and proposes a novel salient region detection method using regional CNN representations. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on improving particular object retrieval, which falls under the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. The use of unsupervised learning for discovering discriminative patterns in the dataset suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of CNN representations, which is a common technique in Multimedia (cs.MM) research. Finally, the paper proposes a method for improving image retrieval, which is a task commonly associated with Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
